Instruction: With the battery inserted and all module switches in the ON position, measure the voltage on Control Module 3’s internal 12V line at three points: (1) at the input terminals inside the box, (2) on the switch input side, and (3) on the switch output side. Also verify whether the red indicator LED in module 3 has 12V across it when the switch is ON. This will determine whether the module’s switch or internal traces are open, or if only the LED branch is faulty.
